Sentencas: Substitution of anions such as F- and Cl- can effectively improve the stability of proton-conducting electrolytes at no expense to proton conduction.
Titulo: A Stable and Efficient Cathode for Fluorine-Containing Proton-Conducting Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: However, during operation, F- and Cl- in electrolytes can transfer to the cathodes, which reduces the stability of the electrolytes.
Titulo: A Stable and Efficient Cathode for Fluorine-Containing Proton-Conducting Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
A Stable and Efficient Cathode for Fluorine-Containing Proton-Conducting Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: [Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O2.9-delta F0.1 (F- BSCF)] was prepared as a potential cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells with BaCe0.8Sm0.2F0.1O2.85 electrolyte.
Titulo: A Stable and Efficient Cathode for Fluorine-Containing Proton-Conducting Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The incorporation of F- in the cathode depressed F- diffusion from the electrolyte and improved the stability of button cells.
Titulo: A Stable and Efficient Cathode for Fluorine-Containing Proton-Conducting Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Temperature-changing X-ray photoelectron spectroscopy and electronic conductivity relaxation results demonstrated that the incorporation of F- enhanced the oxygen incorporation kinetics at intermediate temperatures and improved the cathode catalytic performance.
Titulo: A Stable and Efficient Cathode for Fluorine-Containing Proton-Conducting Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Moreover, a button cell prepared with this novel cathode was stable for 270 h at a current density of 300 mA cm(-2) and 700 degrees C, which was much superior than those containing a BSCF cathode.
Titulo: A Stable and Efficient Cathode for Fluorine-Containing Proton-Conducting Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
